            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627987890281-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Pat the <strong>cod fillets</strong> dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong> and season them with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cod fillets</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627987897926-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627987897926-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627987897926-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627987897926-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627987897926-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fish is cooking, dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli brown rice</strong> to a large, heatproof bowl and put the bowl in the<strong> microwave</strong> for 2-3 min or until piping hot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
